title: GIRLS SWIMMING: Wildcats repeat as FL champs
text:
GIRLS SWIMMING: Wildcats repeat as FL champs Times Sports Staff Finger Lakes Times | 0 comments 
GORHAM — Two teams have risen to the top of the Finger Lakes girls swimming standings in recent years: Marcus Whitman and Palmyra-Macedon. 
The Wildcats and Red Raiders hit the pool once again Tuesday with the league title on the line. And, for the second consecutive season, Marcus Whitman came out on top. 
The Wildcats pulled away late with three straight victories to post a 99-86 win and clinch at least a share of the Finger Lakes crown. 
Marcus Whitman (7-1, 5-0) has won five league championships since 2009. 
“Our girls swam great tonight,” Marcus Whitman coach Marcy Adams said. “They came into the season with big goals, and one was achieved tonight. With one more dual meet to go, the girls are really hoping for a 6-0 record in the league. 
“We had a lot of depth tonight, which helped us clinch the win. We had a lot of close races and best times. I really couldn’t be prouder to coach such a motivated team.” 
Leading by three with four events left, Marcus Whitman’s 200-yard freestyle relay team of Morgan Smithling, Aislinn Coleman, Charlotte Mineo and Courtney Copper inflated the lead to nine points with a victory. 
Copper followed with a 100 backstroke win; she took the 200 individual medley earlier in the meet. Hailey Rossi completed the run with a triumph in the 100 breaststroke. 
Rossi also topped the field in the 50 freestyle. 
Rachael Mayou secured wins in the 200 freestyle and 500 freestyle for the Red Raiders (4-2, 3-1), who won back-to-back league titles in 2012-13. 
NR-W/Red Creek 98, Geneva 78 
GENEVA — Brooke Morrisseau took first in the IM and 500 freestyle for North Rose-Wolcott/Red Creek (3-3, 1-3). 
Laura Vrabel captured the butterfly and breaststroke for Geneva (0-6, 0-4). 
Gananda 91 1⁄2, Midlakes 82 1⁄2 
WALWORTH — Darby McNamara posted a personal-best time of 5:46.84 to win the 500 freestyle for Gananda (3-5, 2-3). McNamara also topped the 100 backstroke. 
Lauren Johnson (200 freestyle, butterfly), Grace Cunningham (IM, breaststroke) and Krista Willard (50 and 100 free) picked up a pair of wins, also. 
The foursome of Hazel Kettlecamp, Georgia White, Riley Backus and Bailey Mahoney touched first in the 400 freestyle relay for Midlakes (2-3). 
MONROE COUNTY EAST 
Victor 113, Canandaigua 73 
VICTOR — Kaitlyn Ringhoff (50 free) and Sabrina Turek (500 free) collected victories to lead the Braves (3-2, 0-2).
